Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into 6 wedges) into 6 wedges. Trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed, quarter lengthways and chopped into roughly 5cm long batons), quarter lengthways and then chop into roughly 5cm long batons. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core removed and sliced into 1cm wide strips), remove the core and slice into 1cm wide strips. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all), stalks and all.

Put the @British chicken breasts{2} in a #bowl{} with a glug of @oil{} and half the @dried thyme{1%tsp}. Season with @salt and @pepper. Massage the seasoning into your chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the red onion, carrot and pepper on a baking tray. Sprinkle on the remaining dried thyme, add a glug of @oil{} and season with @salt and @pepper. Toss to coat the veggies then roast in your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Lay in the chicken breasts and cook until browned on both sides, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once browned, transfer to your baking tray on top of the veggies and cook for the remaining ~{15-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Don't wash your pan - you need it again in a minute!

When the chicken has 10 minutes left to cook, add the @chorizo{90%g} to the baking tray.

Whilst the chicken is roasting, add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} to the chicken frying pan, bring to a boil then reduce the heat to a simmer. Add the @fresh chilli jam{1} and bubble the mixture until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Once cooked, remove the chicken, veg and wedges from your oven. Cut each chicken breast into five slices. Combine the wedges, vegetables, chorizo and chopped parsley together on one of the #baking trays{}, then spoon onto plates. Arrange the chicken on top and reheat the sweet chilli glaze if needed. Spoon the sweet chilli glaze over the chicken and enjoy!